Class MXMLClassDefinitionNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.common.SourceLocation
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.as.NodeBase
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.mxml.MXMLNodeBase
          • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.tree.mxml.MXMLClassDefinitionNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISourceLocation, IASNode, ICommonClassNode, IDefinitionNode, IDocumentableDefinitionNode, IScopedDefinitionNode, IScopedNode, ITypeNode, IMXMLClassDefinitionNode, IMXMLClassReferenceNode, IMXMLNode
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MXMLDocumentNode

    public class MXMLClassDefinitionNode
extends MXMLNodeBase
implements IMXMLClassDefinitionNode, IScopedNode
    MXMLClassDefinitionNode represents an MXML tag which defines a new class. It might be the document tag, or the tag inside a <Component> tag, or the tag inside a <Definition> tag.
